msgctxt "Feature/&AdditionalDamagePatronHiveWeakeningPheromonesTitle"
msgid "Weakening Pheromones"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AdditionalDamagePatronHiveWeakeningPheromonesDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at 1st level, each turn, the first creature you damage with a spell "
"will have disadvantage on their next saving throw. This condition expires on "
"its own after 1 min."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronHiveMagicCounterTitle"
msgid "Magic Counter"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronHiveMagicCounterDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 6th level, you can cast Counterspell once per short rest as "
"a feature. This does not use one of your spellcasting slots, and you add "
"your proficiency bonus when countering level-4 and higher spells."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronHiveReactiveCarapaceTitle"
msgid "Reactive Carapace"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronHiveReactiveCarapaceDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 10th level, whenever you take damage from a spell or magic "
"effect, you can use your reaction to immediately gain a number of temporary "
"hit points equal to 1d8 + CHA modifier. These temporary hit points last "
"until the start of your next turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&DamageAffinityPatronTreePiercingBranchTitle"
msgid "Piercing Branch"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&DamageAffinityPatronTreePiercingBranchDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 1st level, small piercing branches sprout from your skin. "
"Whenever an enemy hits you with a melee attack, they take 1d4 piercing "
"damage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetPatronTreeBlessingOfTheTreeTitle"
msgid "Blessing of the Tree"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetPatronTreeBlessingOfTheTreeDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 6th level, both your blood and your skin start changing "
"color ever so slightly. You can't be poisoned, and you gain resistance "
"against poison and necrotic damage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronTreeExplosiveGrowthTitle"
msgid "Explosive Growth"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronTreeExplosiveGrowthDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 10th level, once per short rest, you can erupt and cause 1d4 "
"per level of piercing damage, push away, and restrain all creatures "
"surrounding you on a failed dexterity save."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AdditionalDamagePatronTimekeeperCurseOfTimeTitle"
msgid "Curse of Time"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AdditionalDamagePatronTimekeeperCurseOfTimeDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 1st level, whenever you damage an opponent with a spell, "
"they become afflicted with the Curse of Time.\n"
" Enemies under the Curse of Time take half your proficiency bonus (rounded "
"up) force damage at the start of their turn for the next minute."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronTimekeeperTimeWarpTitle"
msgid "Time Warp"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronTimekeeperTimeWarpDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 14th level, on your turn, you can take one additional action "
"on top of your regular action and a possible bonus action.\n"
" Once you use this feature, you must finish a long rest before you can use "
"it again."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronTimekeeperAccelerateTitle"
msgid "Accelerate"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronTimekeeperAccelerateDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 10th level, on your turn, you can use a bonus action to "
"briefly accelerate an ally within 6 cells. They gain the effect of Haste "
"until the start of your next turn; however, they do not suffer from lethargy "
"when Accelerate ends.\n"
" You can use this feature a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus "
"per long rest."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronTimekeeperTimeShiftTitle"
msgid "Time Shift"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerPatronTimekeeperTimeShiftDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 6th level, when you are about to take damage, you can use "
"your reaction to project your body forward a few seconds, negating any "
"damage and effects. You are considered banished until the start of your next "
"turn.\n"
"After you use this feature, you can't use it again until you complete a long "
"rest."
msgstr ""

