msgctxt "Feature/&BardExpertiseTitle"
msgid "Bard Expertise"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardExpertiseDescription"
msgid ""
"At the 3rd level, choose two of your skill proficiencies. Your proficiency "
"bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses either of the "
"chosen proficiencies. At the 10th level, you can choose another two skill "
"proficiencies to gain this benefit."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardCollegesTitle"
msgid "Bard Colleges"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardCollegesDescription"
msgid ""
"At the 3rd level, you delve into the advanced techniques of a bard college "
"of your choice, which grants you features at the 3rd level and again at the "
"6th and 14th levels."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PointPoolCollegeLoreBonusSkillsTitle"
msgid "Bonus Proficiencies"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PointPoolCollegeLoreBonusSkillsDescription"
msgid ""
"When you join the College of Lore at the 3rd level, you gain proficiency "
"with three skills of your choice."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerCollegeLoreCuttingWordsTitle"
msgid "Cutting Words"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerCollegeLoreCuttingWordsDescription"
msgid ""
"As a bonus action, you can spend one use of Bardic Inspiration and target a "
"creature that you can see within 12 cells. Roll a Bardic Inspiration die. "
"Until the start of your next turn, the target creature decreases all its "
"ability checks, and attack and damage rolls by the value of the Bardic "
"Inspiration die."
msgstr ""

