msgid "Monk tools"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&SlowFallTitle"
msgid "Slow Fall"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&SlowFallDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 4th level, you can use your reaction when you fall to reduce "
"any fall damage you take by an amount equal to five times your monk level. "
"Additionally, you don't become prone when landing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkUnarmoredDefenseDescription"
msgid ""
"When you are not wearing armor, your armor class equals 10 + your dexterity "
"modifier + your wisdom modifier. You cannot use a shield to gain this "
"benefit."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AdditionalActionMonkMartialArtsTitle"
msgid "Martial Arts - Bonus Unarmed Strike"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AdditionalActionMonkMartialArtsDescription"
msgid ""
"When you use the Attack action with an unarmed strike or a monk weapon on "
"your turn, you can make one unarmed strike as a bonus action."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttackModifierMonkMartialArtsTitle"
msgid "Martial Arts"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttackModifierMonkMartialArtsDescription"
msgid ""
"You can roll a d4 in place of the normal damage of your unarmed strike or "
"monk weapon. This die changes as you gain monk levels (d6 at the 5th level, "
"d8 at the 11th level). You can use dexterity instead of strength for the "
"attack and damage rolls of your unarmed strikes and monk weapons."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&UnarmoredMovementTitle"
msgid "Unarmored Movement"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&UnarmoredMovementDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 2nd level, your speed increases by 2 cells while you're not "
"wearing armor or wielding a shield. This bonus becomes 3 cells at level 6, 4 "
"cells at level 10, and 5 cells at level 14)."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardSongOfRestTitle"
msgid "Song of Rest"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardSongOfRestDescription"
msgid ""
"During a short rest, each ally rolls an additional hit die when spending hit "
"die to regain hit points."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PointPoolMagicalSecretsTitle"
msgid "Magical Secrets"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PointPoolMagicalSecretsDescription"
msgid "Choose two spells from any class and include them in your spell list."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkStillnessOfMindTitle"
msgid "Stillness of Mind"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkStillnessOfMindDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 7th level, you become immune to being charmed or frightened."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkPurityOfBodyTitle"
msgid "Purity of Body"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkPurityOfBodyDescription"
msgid ""
"At the 10th level, your mastery of the Ki flowing through you makes you "
"immune to disease and poison."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkUnarmoredMovementImprovedTitle"
msgid "Unarmored Movement - Improved"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkUnarmoredMovementImprovedDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 9th level, climbing becomes second nature to you. Climbing "
"no longer costs you extra movement."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PatientDefenseTitle"
msgid "Patient Defense"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PatientDefenseDescription"
msgid ""
"You can spend 1 Ki point to take the Dodge action as a bonus action on your "
"turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&StepOfTheWindDisengageTitle"
msgid "Step of the Wind - Disengage"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&StepOfTheWindDisengageDescription"
msgid ""
"You can spend 1 Ki point to take the Disengage action as a bonus action on "
"your turn, and your jump distance is increased for the turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&StepOfTheWindDashTitle"
msgid "Step of the Wind - Dash"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&StepOfTheWindDashDescription"
msgid ""
"You can spend 1 Ki point to take the Dash action as a bonus action on your "
"turn, and your jump distance is increased for the turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkKiEmpoweredStrikesTitle"
msgid "Ki-Empowered Strikes"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkKiEmpoweredStrikesDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 6th level, your unarmed strikes count as magical for the "
"purposes of overcoming resistance and immunity to non-magical attacks and "
"damage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkStunningStrikeShortTitle"
msgid "Stunning Strike"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkStunningStrikeTitle"
msgid "Stunning Strike"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkStunningStrikeDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 5th level, you can interfere with the flow of Ki in an "
"opponent's body. When you hit another creature with a melee weapon attack, "
"you can spend 1 Ki point to attempt a stunning strike. The target must "
"succeed on a constitution saving throw or be stunned until the end of your "
"next turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkEvasionTitle"
msgid "Evasion"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&MonkEvasionDescription"
msgid ""
"At the 7th level, your instinctive agility lets you dodge out of the way of "
"certain area effects, such as a blue dragon's lightning breath or a fireball "
"spell. When you are subjected to an effect that allows you to make a "
"dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage "
"if you succeed on the saving throw, and only half damage if you fail."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkDeflectMissilesTitle"
msgid "Deflect Missiles"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkDeflectMissilesDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 3rd level, you can use your reaction to deflect or catch the "
"missile when you are hit by a ranged weapon attack. When you do so, the "
"damage you take from the attack is reduced by 1d10 + your dexterity modifier "
"+ your monk level.\n"
" If you reduce the damage to 0, you can catch the missile if it is small "
"enough for you to hold in one hand and you have at least one hand free. If "
"you catch a missile in this way, you can spend 1 Ki point to make a ranged "
"attack with the weapon or piece of ammunition you just caught, as part of "
"the same reaction. You make this attack with proficiency, regardless of your "
"weapon proficiencies, and the missile counts as a monk weapon for the "
"attack, which has a normal range of 4 cells and a long range of 12 cells."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkTimelessBodyTitle"
msgid "Timeless Body"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkTimelessBodyDescription"
msgid ""
"At the 15th level, you gain the following benefits:\n"
" - Resistance to necrotic damage\n"
" - Advantage on saving throws against being Life Drained\n"
" - You don't require a food ration anymore to take a long rest"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&TraditionOpenHandWholenessOfBodyTitle"
msgid "Wholeness of Body"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&TraditionOpenHandWholenessOfBodyDescription"
msgid ""
"At the 6th level, you gain the ability to heal yourself. As an action, you "
"can regain hit points equal to three times your monk level. You must finish "
"a long rest before you can use this feature again."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardSpellcastingTitle"
msgid "Bard Spellcasting"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&CastSpellBardDescription"
msgid "Cast bard spells."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardJackOfAllTradesTitle"
msgid "Jack of All Trades"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardJackOfAllTradesDescription"
msgid ""
"Add half your proficiency bonus to any ability check you make that doesn't "
"already include your proficiency bonus."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerBardGiveBardicInspirationTitle"
msgid "Bardic Inspiration"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerBardGiveBardicInspirationDescription"
msgid ""
"Use a bonus action to grant a Bardic Inspiration die to a creature, which "
"can be used within 10 minutes to change the outcome of an attack, saving "
"throw, or ability check. The die value increases at higher levels. Can be "
"used a number of times equal to your CHA modifier per long rest."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttributeModifierBardicInspirationDieD6Title"
msgid "Bardic Inspiration (D6)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttributeModifierBardicInspirationDieD6Description"
msgid "Your Bardic Inspiration die starts as a D6."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttributeModifierBardicInspirationDieD8Title"
msgid "Bardic Inspiration (D8)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttributeModifierBardicInspirationDieD8Description"
msgid "Your Bardic Inspiration die is now a D8."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttributeModifierBardicInspirationDieD10Title"
msgid "Bardic Inspiration (D10)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttributeModifierBardicInspirationDieD10Description"
msgid "Your Bardic Inspiration die is now a D10."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttributeModifierBardicInspirationDieD12Title"
msgid "Bardic Inspiration (D12)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttributeModifierBardicInspirationDieD12Description"
msgid "Your Bardic Inspiration die is now a D12."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerBardCountercharmTitle"
msgid "Countercharm"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerBardCountercharmDescription"
msgid ""
"Start a performance that lasts until the end of your next turn. During that "
"time, all allies within 6 cells have advantage on saving throws against "
"being frightened or charmed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionSurvivalDefensiveStanceTitle"
msgid "Defensive Stance"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionSurvivalDefensiveStanceDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 3rd level, you gain a +2 bonus to AC while you are not "
"wearing armor and are not incapacitated. When you use Patient Defense, you "
"gain advantage to your attack rolls until the start of your next turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&TraditionSurvivalPatientDefenseTitle"
msgid "Patient Defense - Improved"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&TraditionSurvivalPatientDefenseDescription"
msgid ""
"Additionally, you gain advantage to your attack rolls until the start of "
"your next turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttackModifierTraditionSurvivalUnmovingStrengthTitle"
msgid "Unmoving Strength"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AttackModifierTraditionSurvivalUnmovingStrengthDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 11th level, you now add your CON modifier to the damage "
"rolls of your unarmed strikes and monk weapons."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerFlurryOfBlowsFreedomTitle"
msgid "Unending Strikes"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerFlurryOfBlowsFreedomDescription"
msgid ""
"When using Flurry of Blows, your unmatched speed gives you an additional "
"blow for a total of 3."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionSurvivalUnbreakableBodyTitle"
msgid "Unbreakable Body"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionSurvivalUnbreakableBodyDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 6th level, whenever you take damage from any source, you "
"heal a number of hit point equal to your proficiency bonus at the start of "
"your next turn. Whenever you use Patient Defense, you also gain resistance "
"to all damage types until the start of your next turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&TraditionSurvivalPatientDefenseImprovedTitle"
msgid "Patient Defense - Improved II"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&TraditionSurvivalPatientDefenseImprovedDescription"
msgid ""
"You can spend 1 Ki point to take the Dodge action as a bonus action on your "
"turn. When doing so, you gain advantage to your attack rolls and resistance "
"to all damage types until the start of your next turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardFontOfInspirationTitle"
msgid "Font of Inspiration"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardFontOfInspirationDescription"
msgid ""
"You regain all your expended uses of Bardic Inspiration when you finish a "
"short or long rest."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&RitualCastingSelectedTitle"
msgid "Ritual Casting"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&RitualCastingSelectedDescription"
msgid ""
"You can cast a selected spell as a ritual if the spell has the ritual tag."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkFlurryOfBlowsTitle"
msgid "Flurry of Blows"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkFlurryOfBlowsDescription"
msgid ""
"After the Attack action has been used on your turn, you can spend 1 Ki point "
"to make two unarmed strikes as a bonus action."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionFreedomFlurryOfBlowsSwiftStepsTitle"
msgid "Flurry of Blows - Improved I"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionFreedomFlurryOfBlowsSwiftStepsDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 3rd level, whenever you use Flurry of Blows you gain "
"advantage on your next attack, and you gain the benefit of the Dash action "
"until the end of your turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionFreedomFlurryOfBlowsUnendingStrikesTitle"
msgid "Flurry of Blows - Improved II"
msgstr ""

msgctxt ""
"Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionFreedomFlurryOfBlowsUnendingStrikesDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 11th level, when you use Flurry of Blows, you can make up to "
"one additional attack with it (up to a total of 3 flurry of blows attacks)."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkStepOfTheWindTitle"
msgid "Step of the Wind"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetMonkStepOfTheWindDescription"
msgid ""
"You can spend 1 ki point to take the Disengage or Dash action as a bonus "
"action on your turn, and your jump distance is doubled for the turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&ActionAffinityTraditionFreedomSwirlingDanceTitle"
msgid "Swirling Dance"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&ActionAffinityTraditionFreedomSwirlingDanceDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 6th level, when a creature misses you with a melee attack "
"roll, you can use your reaction to make an immediate attack against that "
"creature."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionOpenHandTranquilityTitle"
msgid "Tranquility"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionOpenHandTranquilityDescription"
msgid ""
"At level 11, when you are about to be hit by an attack or single target "
"spell, you can spend one Ki point to gain the benefits of the spell Shield."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionOpenHandOpenHandTechniqueTitle"
msgid "Open Hand Technique"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionOpenHandOpenHandTechniqueDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting when you choose this tradition at the 3rd level, you can manipulate "
"your enemy's Ki when you harness your own. Whenever you hit a creature with "
"one of the attacks granted by your Flurry of Blows, you can impose one of "
"the following effects on that target:\n"
" * It must succeed on a dexterity saving throw or be knocked prone.\n"
" * It must make a strength saving throw. If it fails, you can push it up to "
"3 cells away from you.\n"
" * It can't take reactions until the end of your next turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionOpenHandOpenHandTechniqueDazzleTitle"
msgid "Dazzle"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionOpenHandOpenHandTechniqueDazzleDescription"
msgid "Your target cannot use reactions until the end of your next turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionOpenHandOpenHandTechniqueKnockProneTitle"
msgid "Knock Prone"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionOpenHandOpenHandTechniqueKnockProneDescription"
msgid ""
"Your target must succeed on a dexterity saving throw or be knocked prone."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionOpenHandOpenHandTechniquePushAwayTitle"
msgid "Push Away"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionOpenHandOpenHandTechniquePushAwayDescription"
msgid ""
"Your target must make a strength saving throw. If they fail, you can push "
"them up to 3 cells away from you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&CollegeHopeWanderingHealerSpellsTitle"
msgid "Wandering Healer"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&CollegeHopeWanderingHealerSpellsDescription"
msgid "On your list: {0}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerHornOfBlastingTitle"
msgid "Blow the Horn"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerHornOfBlastingDescription"
msgid ""
"Emits a thunderous blast in a 6-cell cone. All creatures in the cone will "
"take damage, and can become Deafened."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&DragonbornLanguagesTitle"
msgid "Languages"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&DragonbornLanguagesDescription"
msgid "Common, Draconic"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&DragonbornDamageResistanceTitle"
msgid "Damage Resistance"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&DragonbornDamageResistanceDescription"
msgid ""
"You have resistance to the damage type associated with your draconic "
"ancestry."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetDragonbornDraconicChoiceTitle"
msgid "Draconic Ancestry"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetDragonbornDraconicChoiceDescription"
msgid ""
"Select the type of (and associated damage type) of your draconic ancestry."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&DragonbornAbilityScoreIncreaseDescription"
msgid "Strength +2, Charisma +1"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&SpellAttackModifierPlusOneDescription"
msgid "Increases Spell Attack by 1"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&SpellAttackModifierPlusTwoDescription"
msgid "Increases Spell Attack by 2"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AncestryDragonbornDraconicDescription"
msgid "Your draconic ancestry gives you an affinity to a specific damage type."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AncestryDragonbornDraconicBlackTitle"
msgid "Black - Acid"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AncestryDragonbornDraconicBlueTitle"
msgid "Blue - Lightning"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AncestryDragonbornDraconicGoldTitle"
msgid "Gold - Fire"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AncestryDragonbornDraconicGreenTitle"
msgid "Green - Poison"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&AncestryDragonbornDraconicSilverTitle"
msgid "Silver - Cold"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetDragonbornBreathWeaponTitle"
msgid "Breath Weapon"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetDragonbornBreathWeaponDescription"
msgid ""
"You can use your action to exhale destructive energy based on your draconic "
"ancestry."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponBlackTitle"
msgid "Breath Weapon - Acid Line"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponBlueTitle"
msgid "Breath Weapon - Lightning Line"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponGoldTitle"
msgid "Breath Weapon - Fire Cone"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponGreenTitle"
msgid "Breath Weapon - Poison Cone"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponSilverTitle"
msgid "Breath Weapon - Cold Cone"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponBlackDescription"
msgid ""
"Project acid in a line of 1 cell in width and 6 cells in length. Creatures "
"in the line must make a CON saving throw to halve the acid damage. The "
"damage is equal to 2D6 at level 1 to 5, 3D6 from level 11 to 15, and 4D6 "
"above."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponBlueDescription"
msgid ""
"Project lightning in a line of one cell in width and six cells in length. "
"Creatures in the line must make a CON saving throw to halve the lightning "
"damage. The damage is equal to 2d6 up to level 5, increasing to 3d6 at level "
"6, 4d6 at level 11, and 5d6 at level 16."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponGoldDescription"
msgid ""
"Project fire in a cone 3 cells wide. Creatures in the cone must make a DEX "
"saving throw to halve the fire damage. The damage is equal to 2d6 up to "
"level 5, increasing to 3d6 at level 6, 4d6 at level 11, and 5d6 at level 16."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponGreenDescription"
msgid ""
"Project poison in a cone 3 cells wide. Creatures in the cone must make a DEX "
"saving throw to halve the poison damage. The damage is equal to 2d6 up to "
"level 5, increasing to 3d6 at level 6, 4d6 at level 11, and 5d6 at level 16."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerDragonbornBreathWeaponSilverDescription"
msgid ""
"Project ice in a cone 3 cells wide. Creatures in the cone must make a DEX "
"saving throw to halve the cold damage. The damage is equal to 2d6 up to "
"level 5, increasing to 3d6 at level 6, 4d6 at level 11, and 5d6 at level 16."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&DieRollModifierAuraOfPreeminenceTitle"
msgid "Aura of Preeminence"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&DieRollModifierAuraOfPreeminenceDescription"
msgid ""
"When you make an Intimidation or Insight check, you can treat a roll of 9 or "
"lower as a 10."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerBardWordsOfHopeTitle"
msgid "Words of Hope"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerBardWordsOfHopeDescription"
msgid ""
"When giving a Bardic Inspiration die to an ally, they also roll a Song of "
"Rest die to heal up to half their maximum health."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardHopeHealingBalladTitle"
msgid "Healing Ballad"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardHopeHealingBalladDescription"
msgid ""
"Song of Rest heals additional hit points equal to your charisma modifier. At "
"the end of a short rest, it also grants allies temporary hit points equal to "
"one Bardic Inspiration die plus your charisma modifier."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardTraditionVerbalOnslaughtTitle"
msgid "Verbal Onslaught"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&BardTraditionVerbalOnslaughtDescription"
msgid ""
"As a reaction, after a creature you can see within 12 cells damages you, you "
"can expend one of your Bardic Inspiration. On a failed intelligence saving "
"throw, they take psychic damage equal to 2x your bardic inspiration die + "
"charisma modifier and be stunned until the end of their next turn. The "
"damage is halved on a successful saving throw."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionLightLuminousKiTitle"
msgid "Luminous Ki"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionLightLuminousKiDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 3rd level, you learn the Light & Shine cantrips (wisdom for "
"spellcasting).\n"
" Whenever you hit a creature with one of the attacks granted by your Flurry "
"of Blows, they automatically start emitting bright light until the end of "
"your next turn."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&TraditionLightSpellcastingTitle"
msgid "Monk (Way of Light) Spellcasting"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&TraditionLightSpellcastingDescription"
msgid "Can cast Shine and Light cantrips."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionLightRadiantStrikesTitle"
msgid "Radiant Strikes"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&FeatureSetTraditionLightRadiantStrikesDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 6th level, any time you strike a target affected by Shine or "
"Luminous Ki, you deal an additional 1d4 radiant damage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionLightBlindingFlashTitle"
msgid "Blinding Flash"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "Feature/&PowerTraditionLightBlindingFlashDescription"
msgid ""
"Starting at the 11th level, as a bonus action, you can spend 2 Ki points to "
"generate a blinding burst of light. All creatures within 3 cells of you must "
"roll a CON saving throw or take 3d6 radiant damage, and become blinded until "
"the end of your next turn (half damage on success)."
msgstr ""

